https://confluence.atlassian.com/adminjiracloud/importing-issues-776636788.html states:

{quote}
We recommend being on the latest release of JIRA Server when importing to JIRA Cloud to avoid any problems with the importing of the XML backup. Check out Upgrading JIRA applications to help you upgrade to the latest version. You can sign up for a new JIRA Cloud site here.
{quote}

Strictly speaking JIRA only needs to be > 7.0, upgrading should be unnecessary past that point.

Could we please update the note to say that it just needs to be version 7.0 or greater. Also, we can probably remove the mention to JIRA 4.4 since that was released about 5 years ago.

Hello,

as a Developer I have to link every our checking with a JIRA link. What I usually do I copy JIRA code + JIRA issue title.

 

!image-2017-10-18-12-43-18-334.png!

 

It gets copied like this.

 
{code:java}
    DEVAPI-195

[AUDITEVENT] Update to Spring Boot 1.5.8
{code}
I would appreciate to have some copy to clipboard icon where the text would be like following:
{code:java}
DEVAPI-195 [AUDITEVENT] Update to Spring Boot 1.5.8
{code}
Thanks!

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
*NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Cloud*. Using *JIRA Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRASERVER-29072].
{panel}
Currently JIRA issue can be linked to remote application. In the Issue Navigator, the Link column will only shows the link to the issues in the same instance. It's should also be able to display the remote link for the issue. Or a separated system field should collect them!
